<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1328,1838]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1328,1354]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Discussion.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[442,626,1329,1354]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,626,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently contains 
<number box="[866,896,1329,1355]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="22.0">22</number>
described species, with one subspecies. As species were steadily added to the genus since its inception, and following the tentative placement of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,338,1403,1428]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,338,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[357,404,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">s. l.</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[423,545,1403,1428]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="childressi">
<emphasis box="[423,545,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">childressi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[594,889,1403,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Gustafson, R. G., Turner, R. D., Lutz, R. A. &amp; Vrijenhoek, R. C. (1998) A new genus and five new species of mussels (Bivalvia, Mytilidae) from deep-sea sulfide / hydrocarbon seeps in the Gulf of Mexico. Malacologia, 40, 63 - 112." type="journal article">
Gustafson 
<emphasis box="[729,794,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[812,880,1403,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cosel" box="[903,1067,1403,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Cosel, R. von (2002) A new species of bathymodioline mussel (Mollusca, Bivalvia, Mytilidae) from Mauritania (West Africa), with comments on the genus Bathymodiolus Kenk &amp; Wilson, 1985. Zoosystema, 24, 259 - 271." type="journal article" year="2002">
Cosel (
<number box="[992,1058,1403,1429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
instigated an overhaul of the taxonomic status of the genus, dividing it into several groups based upon a number of shell and anatomical features. These features included the form of the posterior retractor, umbonal placement, and placement of the anterior retractor scar relative to the umbonal cavity. This study has since been bolstered by molecular analyses of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Miyazaki" box="[428,687,1552,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Miyazaki, J. - I., Shintaku, M., Kyuno, A., Fujiwara, Y., Hashimoto, J. &amp; Iwasaki, H. (2004) Phylogenetic relationships of deep-sea mussels of the genus Bathymodiolus (Bivalvia: Mytilidae). Marine Biology, 144, 527 - 535." type="journal article" year="2004">
Miyazaki 
<emphasis box="[553,607,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[623,687,1552,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Jones and Vrijenhoek 
<number box="[971,1035,1552,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; Jones 
<emphasis box="[1124,1186,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1195,1259,1552,1578]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2006.0">2006</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Iwasaki" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Iwasaki, H., Kyuno, A., Shintaku, M., Fujita, Y., Fujiwara, Y., Fujikura, K., Hashimoto, J., Oliveira Martins, L. de, Gebruk, A. &amp; Miyazaki, J. - I. (2006) Evolutionary relationships of deep-sea mussels inferred by mitochondrial DNA sequences. Marine Biology, 149, 1111 - 1122." type="journal article" year="2006">
Iwasaki 
<emphasis box="[1374,1436,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[151,213,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Samadi" box="[226,451,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Samadi, S., Quemere, E., Lorion, J., Tillier, A., Cosel, R. von, Lopez, P., Cruaud, C., Couloux, A. &amp; Boisselier-Dubayle, M. - C. (2007) Molecular phylogeny in mytilids supports the wooden steps to deep-sea vents hypothesis. Comptes Rendus Biologies, 330, 446 - 456." type="journal article" year="2007">
Samadi 
<emphasis box="[321,381,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[389,451,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genio" box="[463,672,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Genio, L., Johnson, S. B., Vrijenhoek, R. C., Cunha, M. R., Tyler, P. A., Kiel, S. &amp; Little, C. T. S. (2008) New record of &quot; Bathymodiolus &quot; mauritanicus Cosel 2002 from the Gulf of Cadiz (NE Atlantic) mud volcanoes. Journal of Shellfish Research, 27, 53 - 61." type="journal article" year="2008">
Génio 
<emphasis box="[543,603,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[610,672,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Won" box="[685,877,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Won, Y. - J., Jones, W. J. &amp; Vrijenhoek, R. C. (2008) Absence of cospeciation between deep-sea mytilids and their thiotrophic endosymbionts. Journal of Shellfish Research, 27, 129 - 138." type="journal article" year="2008">
Won 
<emphasis box="[748,807,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[815,877,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fujita" box="[890,1096,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Fujita, Y., Matsumoto, H., Fujiwara, Y., Hashimoto, J., Galkin, S. V., Ueshima, R. &amp; Miyazaki, J. - I. (2009) Phylogenetic relationships of deep-sea Bathymodiolus mussels to their mytilid relatives from sunken whale carcasses and wood. Venus, 67, 123 - 134." type="journal article" year="2009">
Fujita 
<emphasis box="[966,1026,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1033,1096,1589,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), confirming its paraphyletic status. Three clades are currently recognized within the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[894,1071,1626,1651]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[894,1071,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two within 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1399,1626,1651]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1399,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">s. l.</emphasis>
) (the 
<taxonomicName box="[238,387,1664,1689]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aduloides">
<emphasis box="[238,387,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. aduloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[445,592,1664,1689]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="childressi">
<emphasis box="[445,592,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. childressi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clades), and the 
<taxonomicName box="[794,982,1664,1689]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="thermophilus">
<emphasis box="[794,982,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. thermophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, or 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1278,1664,1689]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1101,1278,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1295,1342,1664,1689]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">s. s.</emphasis>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Cosel" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Cosel, R. von &amp; Janssen, R. (2008) Bathymodioline mussels of the Bathymodiolus (s. l.) childressi clade from methane seeps near Edison Seamount, New Ireland, Papua New Guinea (Bivalvia: Mytilidae). Archiv fur Molluskenkunde, 137, 195 - 224." type="journal article" year="2008">
Cosel and Janssen 
<number box="[303,369,1700,1726]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The clades are themselves split into smaller groups based upon differences among the above-mentioned features plus consideration of shell size, shape, and form of the anterior margin (
<bibRefCitation author="Cosel" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Cosel, R. von &amp; Janssen, R. (2008) Bathymodioline mussels of the Bathymodiolus (s. l.) childressi clade from methane seeps near Edison Seamount, New Ireland, Papua New Guinea (Bivalvia: Mytilidae). Archiv fur Molluskenkunde, 137, 195 - 224." type="journal article" year="2008">
Cosel and Janssen 
<number box="[248,312,1775,1801]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Several species currently referred to 
<taxonomicName box="[762,938,1775,1800]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Bathymodiolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[762,938,1775,1800]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bathymodiolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[955,997,1775,1800]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">s. l.</emphasis>
) will probably eventually be referred to new genera (see also discussion of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[711,841,1812,1837]" class="Bivalvia" family="Mytilidae" genus="Gigantidas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mytiloida" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,841,1812,1837]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Gigantidas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below).
</paragraph>
